  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Kimberley</strong></p>
<p>On the front side of the mountain beginner skiers and riders can enjoy long, wide open runs perfectly groomed for cruising and carving pleasure.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates skiing in Kimberley</strong></p>
<p>The Easter Bowl is a haven for the more adventurous skier and rider. Here the powder is deeper and lasts longer.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Kimberley</strong></p>
<p>The advanced terrain in the Bowl challenges you with many steep and deep mogul runs.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding in Kimberley</strong></p>
<p>For snowboarders the entire mountain is yours to enjoy. Try the expanded terrain park with its jumps and rails, or enjoy the off piste with plenty of natural obstacles.</p>
<p><strong>Related Links:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/media/13055073/kimberley-alpine-resort.pdf" target="_blank" title="Download your Kimberley Alpine Resort Resort Map">Download your Kimberley Alpine Resort Resort Map</a></li>
</ul>]]></generalInformation>
